Place a sheet of filo pastry on the cutting board. Brush and cover the pastry sheet with butter. Sprinkle some powdered sugar on the pastry sheet and then cover it with another pastry sheet. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/a/a3/Mousse_berries_5_358.PNG","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/a/a3/Mousse_berries_5_358.PNG","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":338,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":559.1022443890274,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.videojug.com/film/how-to-make-white-chocolate-mousse-with-berries">http://www.videojug.com/film/how-to-make-white-chocolate-mousse-with-berries</a> - shared with permission
</p><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p></div>"}  

Flatten the second pastry sheet on the first one by smoothing it down with your hand. Repeat the process with the other sheets. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/b/ba/Mousse_berries_6_666.PNG","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/b/ba/Mousse_berries_6_666.PNG","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.videojug.com/film/how-to-make-white-chocolate-mousse-with-berries">http://www.videojug.com/film/how-to-make-white-chocolate-mousse-with-berries</a> - shared with permission
