Brush the last sheet with butter, sprinkle it with powdered sugar, and turn them all over, exposing the side that was against the cutting board. Now butter and sugar this side as well. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/6/64/Mousse_berries_7_229.PNG","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/6/64/Mousse_berries_7_229.PNG","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":343,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":567.4666666666667,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.videojug.com/film/how-to-make-white-chocolate-mousse-with-berries">http://www.videojug.com/film/how-to-make-white-chocolate-mousse-with-berries</a> - shared with permission
